<content type="str">WESTERLY — Cox Communications has announced the availability of Cox Wi-Fi internet access in downtown Westerly for Cox high speed internet customers. The company said the availability of Wi-Fi downtown will provide thousands of customers the ability to access the web reliably and on-the-go. The coverage provides internet accessibility at key locations, from shops and restaurants to Craig Field, Westerly High School and the Westerly Yacht Club. 
 
State Sen. Dennis Algiere, R-Westerly, and Rep. Brian Patrick Kennedy, D-Westerly, joined Jay Allbaugh, Cox senior vice president and regional manager, to announce the new network on Saturday at the Washington Trust Community Skating Center. 
 
Westerly is the third Wi-Fi location Cox has deployed in Rhode Island. Wi-Fi launched in Providence’s Kennedy Plaza in 2015, followed by Upper and Lower Thames Streets in Newport. The hotspots are part of more than 500,000 that are accessible by customers nationwide. 
   
