With the explosive growth in usage of smartphones, tablets and other mobile connected devices, Cox said that Wi-Fi adds significant value and reliable internet access. Cox customers with Preferred, Premier or Ultimate Internet packages have free access to Cox Wi-Fi as part of their service. 
 
In addition to the Rhode Island locations, Cox customers also have access when they travel, made possible by a collaboration of communications providers across the country, called CableWiFi. The hotspots are located in high-traffic areas such as restaurants, malls, sports arenas, parks and beaches in cities like New York, Washington D.C., Boston, Richmond, Philadelphia, Los Angeles and Tampa. Customers of Comcast, Time Warner, Bright House and Optimum, in turn, will also be able to access Wi-Fi in Westerly, including Comcast customers in Connecticut.</content> 
